Name: wikilon-runtime
Version: 0.1
Synopsis: Wikilon Runtime
Category: Awelon
Description:
  The Wikilon runtime is a high performance runtime for Awelon Bytecode with
  support for larger-than-memory values and persistence. It is written in an
  ad-hoc mix of Haskell and C, with intention to leverage LLVM compilation.
  Large values and persistence are backed by LMDB. This module includes just
  the runtime aspects, any private structure.
  
Author: David Barbour
Maintainer: dmbarbour@gmail.com
Homepage: http://github.com/dmbarbour/wikilon

Package-Url: 
Copyright: (c) 2015 by David Barbour
License: BSD3
license-file: LICENSE.txt 
license-files: 
    csrc/lmdb/LICENSE 
    csrc/lmdb/COPYRIGHT
Stability: experimental
build-type: Simple
cabal-version: >= 1.20

Extra-source-files:
    README.md 
    changelog.md
    csrc/lmdb/lmdb.h
    csrc/lmdb/midl.h
    csrc/lmdb/mdb.c
    csrc/lmdb/midl.c
    csrc/murmur3/murmur3.h
